docs.abstract: A Sunday town hall with Senator Kirsten Gillibrand was another sign of Fox News’s ability to influence the Democratic primary, despite a ban by party leaders.
docs.snippet: A Sunday town hall with Senator Kirsten Gillibrand was another sign of Fox News’s ability to influence the Democratic primary, despite a ban by party leaders.
docs.lead_paragraph: Three months ago, Democratic Party leaders took a stand: Fox News, President Trump’s favorite channel, and a reliable soapbox for attacks on liberals, was barred from participating in the party’s 2020 presidential debates. The move would ice out the network derided by critics as “state TV” from influencing the outcome of the Democratic primary.

headline.main: The Fox News Primary? How Trump’s Favorite Network Became a Democratic Power Player
headline.print_headline: How Fox  Is Infiltrating A Primary

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has concluded his tariff threat worked and forced Mexico to stop the flow of migrants. On Monday, he pivoted back to his trade fight with China and vowed to hit Beijing with more tariffs if it did not accede to America’s trade demands.

headline.main: Trump Says Mexico Tariffs Worked, Emboldening Trade Fight With China
headline.print_headline: Hailing Tariffs As Win, Trump Ponders More

docs.abstract: Britain’s currency has slumped as uncertainty grows over how and when the U.K. will leave the European Union.
docs.snippet: Britain’s currency has slumped as uncertainty grows over how and when the U.K. will leave the European Union.
docs.lead_paragraph: Britain’s currency sank to a two-year low last week, dipping below $1.24 as fears of a no-deal Brexit grew. Long seen as a symbol of Britain’s stability and national pride, the pound has in recent years become a barometer for concerns about the country and its departure from the European Union.

headline.main: The Pound Is a Brexit Barometer. It’s Not Looking Great Right Now.
headline.print_headline: As Brexit Barometer, Pound Looks Rather Peaked
